’’Ł@b77f55815ca7437657ea4804ee2f7321b7c67f75db3dafb58c4a73b226d642c2ŚŲTitle: Integer
Path: Integer
Content:
Description:

Numbers without a fractional component (positive, negative, and 0)
Annotation:

``int``

Literal syntax:

A decimal, hex, octal, or binary numeric value without a decimal place. E.g., 
``-100``
, 
``0``
, 
``50``
, 
``+50``
, 
``0xff``
 (hex), 
``0o234``
 (octal), 
``0b10101``
 (binary)
Casts
:
[link: /commands/docs/into_int.md] ``into int``
See also:

[link: /book/types_of_data.md#integers] Types of Data - Integers
’Ł@961b3b141fe74f9472074eea54b6e05aa3c502c609631e0cfaa489ab006bf92cŁ—Title: Integer
Path: Additional Language Notes
Content:
Integers are internally represented as signed 64-bit numbers with two's-complement arithmetic.
